CAT. NO.

Plants of Tennessee

Diapensiaceae
*Galax urceolata* (Poir.) Brummitt

Tennessee: Cocke County
35.73956° Latitude -83.23954° Longitude 4360 Feet Elevation
Quadrangle: Luftee Knob Cosby Watershed
T. 10S, R. 76E, Sect. 4
The Great Smoky Mountains National Park. Along Snake Den Mountain, the Snake Den
Mountain Trail and below the Maddron Bald Trail. Coordinate Datum: WGS84/NAD83.

On southeast-facing (165°) slope in heath slick with *Acer rubrum*, *Amelanchier*, *Picea rubens*, *Pinus pungens*, *Clethra acuminata*, *Kalmia latifolia*, *Leucothoe recurva*,
*Rhododendron catawbiense*, *Vaccinium* sp., etc.

1 June 2011
